b'' b'[much discussion about switching and drives removed]' b'' b'another (albeit strange) option is using a program like ii' b'(available via anonymous ftp at many major sites), or fdformat' b'(also available via anonymous ftp), that allows you to format' b'5.25hd disks to 1.44meg, or 3.5"hd disks to 1.2meg (along with' b'many many other formats!) so you can diskcopy (yes, the broken' b'messy-dos diskcopy!) the disks onto disks or vice' b'versa... i use this techniques with "non-dos" self-booting' b'game disks on my old tandy and it works... another program' b"named teledisk (shareware--available on many major bbs's) will" b'also make the weird format disks, provided you have ii' b"or fdformat installed.... some disks that won't diskcopy" b"properly can be readily teledisk'd into the proper format..." b'at least this is a software solution for a hardware/bios' b'deficiency, eh?' b'' b'' b'--' b'[====disclaimer--if you believe any of this, check your head!====]' b'------------------------------------------------------------------' b'' b'nuke the whales!' 